{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015vPNsbnN89k8x4Vzo53PNA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding. Let me create a comprehensive report of the visual test setup:\n\n## Visual Test Setup Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough review of the visual test infrastructure, here's what I found:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Test Files Structure**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/`\n\n**Two spec files exist:**\n- **`routes.spec.ts`** - Basic route snapshots (1 test per route)\n- **`states.spec.ts`** - State-variant snapshots (wallet connection states, interactions, etc.)\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Snapshots Archive**\n\n**Location**: `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`\n\n**routes.spec.ts snapshots** (14 routes tested):\n- `404.png`, `home.png`, `fairness.png`, `profile.png`, `quests.png`, `loot.png`, `leaderboard.png`\n- Game pages: `coinflip.png`, `lord-of-rngs.png`, `close-call.png`, `crash.png`, `game-of-trades.png`\n\n**states.spec.ts snapshots** (12 state variants):\n- Home: `home-disconnected.png`, `home-connected.png`\n- Profile: `profile-connected.png`\n- Lord of RNGs: `lotr-lobby-disconnected.png`, `lotr-tier-selected.png`, `lotr-tier-connected.png`, `lotr-back-to-lobby.png`\n- Coinflip: `coinflip-disconnected.png`, `coinflip-connected.png`, `coinflip-error-toast-position.png`\n\n---\n\n### 3. **routes.spec.ts Full Contents**\n\nThe file tests 12 unique routes with a simple pattern:\n1. Navigate to route via `stablePage.goto()`\n2. Capture full-page screenshot\n3. Compare against baseline snapshot\n\nRoutes tested include Close Call at `/close-call` (line 19-22).\n\n**Pattern for each test:**\n```typescript\ntest(\"game name\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/path\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"filename.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **states.spec.ts Full Contents**\n\nThe file tests stateful interactions with nested `test.describe()` blocks organized by page/feature:\n\n**Home page (2 variants):**\n- Wallet disconnected: clears localStorage, captures initial state\n- Wallet connected: clears storage → clicks connect button → waits for connected state → re-injects animation-freeze CSS → waits 300ms → captures\n\n**Profile page (1 variant):**\n- Wallet connected: same flow as home, but with `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.03` (allows 3% pixel drift for avatar SVG sub-pixel rendering variance)\n\n**Lord of RNGs page (4 variants):**\n- Lobby disconnected: no wallet connection\n- Round selected: waits for `.lotr-tier-lobby`, clicks first `.lotr-tier-card`, waits for `.lotr-sidebar`\n- Round selected with wallet connected: connects wallet → selects round → re-injects CSS → waits 300ms\n- Back to lobby: selects round → clicks \"back to lobby\" button → waits for lobby to reappear\n\n**Coinflip page (3 variants):**\n- Wallet disconnected\n- Wallet connected: same flow as home\n- Error toast position: programmatically injects error toast HTML via `evaluate()` to test placement below middle container\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Close-Call Coverage Status**\n\n**INCOMPLETE**\n\nClose Call has coverage in:\n- ✅ `routes.spec.ts` line 19-22: Basic route snapshot (`close-call.png`)\n- ❌ **Missing**: No state-variant tests in `states.spec.ts`\n  - No \"wallet disconnected\" variant\n  - No \"wallet connected\" variant\n  - No interaction/selection tests\n\n**Note:** Route test shows the **route exists** (`/close-call`), and a snapshot was captured on **Mar 18, 05:23** (recently updated).\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Pattern for Adding New Visual Tests**\n\nBased on how **Coinflip** and **Lord of RNGs** are tested:\n\n**For route baselines (simple):**\n```typescript\ntest(\"game-name page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/game-name\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"game-name.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\n**For state variants (complex):**\n```typescript\ntest.describe(\"Game Name page\", () => {\n  test(\"wallet disconnected\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n    await stablePage.addInitScript(() => {\n      localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\");\n    });\n    await stablePage.goto(\"/game-name\");\n    await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"gamename-disconnected.png\", { fullPage: true });\n  });\n\n  test(\"wallet connected\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n    await stablePage.addInitScript(() => {\n      localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\");\n    });\n    await stablePage.goto(\"/game-name\");\n    \n    // Click wallet button\n    await stablePage.locator(\".rng-wallet-button--disconnected\").click();\n    await stablePage.waitForSelector(\".rng-wallet-button--connected\", { timeout: 5000 });\n    \n    // Re-inject CSS to freeze animations\n    await stablePage.addStyleTag({\n      content: `\n        *, *::before, *::after {\n          animation-duration: 0s !important;\n          animation-delay: 0s !important;\n          transition-duration: 0s !important;\n          transition-delay: 0s !important;\n          scroll-behavior: auto !important;\n        }\n        svg { animation-play-state: paused !important; }\n      `,\n    });\n    \n    await stablePage.waitForTimeout(300);\n    await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"gamename-connected.png\", { fullPage: true });\n  });\n\n  // Optional: game-specific interaction tests\n  test(\"some interaction\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n    // ... navigate, interact, capture\n  });\n});\n```\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Fixture System (stablePage)**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n\nThe `stablePage` fixture:\n1. **Deterministic randomness**: Seeds `Math.random()` and `crypto.getRandomValues()` with Mulberry32 PRNG (seed 42)\n2. **Frozen time**: Locks `Date.now()` to `1767225600000` (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n3. **Animation freeze**: Injects CSS to disable all CSS/SVG animations/transitions, pauses SMIL animations\n4. **Network idle**: Wraps `page.goto()` to wait for `networkidle` + fonts.ready + 300ms settle time\n5. **Error filtering**: Collects console errors but ignores expected noise patterns (401, 403, 429, favicon, connection refused, network errors)\n6. **Error assertion**: Throws if any console errors detected after test completes\n\n**Wrapped goto signature:**\n```typescript\npage.goto = async (url: string, options?: Parameters<typeof page.goto>[1]) => {\n  // ... inject CSS + pause SVG animations + wait fonts + 300ms\n  return response;\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 8. **Playwright Configuration**\n\n**File:** `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n\n**Key settings:**\n- **Test dir**: `e2e/`\n- **Project filter**: Only runs tests matching `visual/**/*.spec.ts`\n- **Viewport**: 1280×1080 (Desktop Chrome)\n- **Snapshot threshold**: `maxDiffPixelRatio: 0.015` (1.5% pixel variance default; can be overridden per test)\n- **Snapshot path template**: `{testDir}/__snapshots__/{testFilePath}/{arg}{ext}`\n- **Web server**: Vite on port 3000 (customizable via `PLAYWRIGHT_PLATFORM_PORT`)\n- **Mock mode**: `VITE_MOCK_MODE=true` (simulated data, no backend required)\n- **Retries**: 0 (fail fast)\n- **Workers**: 1 (sequential, deterministic)\n\n---\n\n### 9. **Routes Defined in App.tsx**\n\nClose Call route definitions (lines 376, 385):\n```typescript\n<Route path=\"/close-call\" element={<CloseCallPage />} />\n<Route path=\"/close-call/:roundId\" element={<CloseCallRoundPage />} />\n```\n\nThe `/close-call` route is fully integrated. The `/close-call/:roundId` route supports deep-linking to specific rounds (similar to `/coinflip/:matchId` and `/lord-of-rngs/:matchId`).\n\n---\n\n### 10. **Summary Table: Visual Test Coverage by Game**\n\n| Game | routes.spec.ts | states.spec.ts | Total Snapshots |\n|------|---|---|---|\n| Coinflip | ✅ | ✅ (3 variants) | 4 |\n| Lord of RNGs | ✅ | ✅ (4 variants) | 5 |\n| Close Call | ✅ | ❌ | 1 |\n| Crash | ✅ | ❌ | 1 |\n| Game of Trades | ✅ | ❌ | 1 |\n\n**Close Call is the least covered** — only has the basic route snapshot, missing all state variants.\n\n---\n\n### Key Files Referenced\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/routes.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/visual/states.spec.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.config.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/routes.spec.ts/` (14 .png files)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/states.spec.ts/` (12 .png files)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0e6237c54157a13c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61959\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 96539</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c62976-263f-4cf9-9e61-e0f9f45b35cf","uuid":"a5fa27d6-a717-4598-939f-7a707eba8552","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the visual test setup in the project. I need to understand:\n\n1. What files exist in `apps/platform/e2e/visual/` — read all spec files\n2. What snapshots exist in `apps/platform/e2e/__snapshots__/visual/`\n3. How the routes.spec.ts and states.spec.ts are structured (full contents)\n4. What close-call coverage already exists\n5. What pattern is used for adding new visual tests (look at how coinflip and lord-of-rngs are tested)\n\nBe thorough — read all the spec files and fixture files in the visual test directory.","agentId":"a0e6237c54157a13c","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have a good understanding. Let me create a comprehensive report of the visual test setup:\n\n## Visual Test Setup Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough review of the visual test infrastructure, 