{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q4RnwHp9k8Rw4qk4bmE7TV","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **1. ROUTES**\n\nThe close-call game has **two routes**:\n\n| Route | Component | Purpose |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `/close-call` | `CloseCallPage.tsx` | Main game lobby with bet UI, candlestick chart, history |\n| `/close-call/:roundId` | `CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` | Deep-link to individual completed round details (fairness verification) |\n\n---\n\n### **2. VISUAL STATES FOR `/close-call` (Main Page)**\n\nThe `CloseCallPage` supports multiple visual variations based on context:\n\n#### **A. Wallet State**\n- **Disconnected** — \"Connect Wallet\" button visible in sidebar\n- **Connected** — \"GREEN\" / \"RED\" side selector buttons enabled\n\n#### **B. Betting Window State**\n- **Betting Open** (round.phase === \"open\" && now < bettingEndsAt)\n  - Side selector buttons enabled\n  - Bet amount input enabled\n  - User can place bets\n- **Betting Closed** (now >= bettingEndsAt)\n  - Side selector buttons disabled\n  - Message: \"Betting window closed\"\n- **Round Settled** (round.phase === \"settled\" or \"refunded\")\n  - Result banner displays outcome (GREEN WINS / RED WINS / REFUND)\n  - Pool distribution shows final state\n  - Winners get \"Payout Received!\" message\n\n#### **C. User Bet Status**\n- **No Bet Placed** — pending amount > 0, no userBet\n- **Bet Pending** (placingBet === true) — \"Joining...\" spinner on selected side button\n- **Bet Placed** (userBet !== null) — side button shows selected state, can't place another bet\n- **Round Result** (completedRound !== null) — result banner shows if user won/lost\n\n#### **D. Loading State**\n- **Loading Chart** (loading === true) — spinner + \"Loading chart...\" message\n- **Chart Ready** (recentCandles.length > 0) — candlestick chart renders\n\n#### **E. Chart & Pool States**\n- **Balanced Pool** (greenPool ≈ redPool) — bar split ~50/50\n- **Skewed Pool** (greenPool >> redPool or vice versa) — bar heavily weighted to one side\n- **Chart Progress** (candleProgress 0-1) — current candle progresses toward close\n- **Candlestick Colors** — green candles (close > open), red candles (close < open)\n\n#### **F. Pool Distribution UI**\n- **Pool Bar** — visual split showing GREEN% vs RED%\n- **Odds Display** — multiplier for each side (2.5x, 1.2x, etc.)\n- **Pool Amounts** — total SOL in each side\n\n#### **G. Result Banner (Post-Round)**\n- **Green Wins** (outcome === \"green\") — green banner, \"GREEN WINS\"\n- **Red Wins** (outcome === \"red\") — red banner, \"RED WINS\"\n- **Refund** (outcome === \"refund\") — yellow/gold banner, \"REFUND\"\n- **User Won** — \"You Won!\" + green payout amount\n- **User Lost** — \"You Lost\" + red loss amount\n- **Bet Refunded** — \"Bet refunded\" + no payout shown\n\n#### **H. History Modal**\n- Opened by clicking history entry\n- Shows: Round stats, candle OHLC data, outcome, your payout, oracle verification\n\n---\n\n### **3. VISUAL STATES FOR `/close-call/:roundId` (Round Details Page)**\n\nThis is a **static information page** showing completed round data with minimal state variance:\n\n#### **States:**\n- **Loading** — \"Loading round...\" spinner\n- **Error** (404) — \"Round not found\" message + back link\n- **Success** — Full round details:\n  - Round ID, status, creation time\n  - Oracle prices (open, close, change)\n  - Pool breakdown (green/red amounts and counts)\n  - Entries list (individual bets from both sides)\n  - Settlement info (if settled)\n  - Verification message explaining fairness model\n\n---\n\n### **4. COMPONENT VARIANTS**\n\nKey components with visual variations:\n\n| Component | File | Variations |\n|-----------|------|-----------|\n| **SideSelector** | `SideSelector.tsx` | disabled, selected, placing (spinner), disabled+other-placing |\n| **BetAmountInput** | `BetAmountInput.tsx` | disabled, with different max amounts |\n| **PoolDistribution** | `PoolDistribution.tsx` | pre-round (no outcome), post-round (with outcome highlight), various pool balances |\n| **CandlestickChart** | `CandlestickChart.tsx` | loading, rendering, candle progress, history vs current candle |\n| **RoundResultBanner** | Uses @rng-utopia/ui | green win, red win, refund, user won, user lost |\n\n---\n\n### **5. RECOMMENDED VISUAL TEST COVERAGE**\n\nBased on the pattern from `states.spec.ts`, here are the tests that should be created:\n\n#### **Disconnected User Tests**\n1. **`close-call-page-disconnected`** — Main page, betting open, wallet disconnected\n   - Shows \"Connect Wallet\" button instead of side selector\n\n#### **Connected User — Betting Open (Active Round)**\n2. **`close-call-page-connected-betting-open`** — Wallet connected, round.phase=\"open\", betting window active\n   - Side selector buttons enabled\n   - Bet amount input ready\n   - Pool bar showing current distribution\n   - Chart displaying candles\n\n#### **Connected User — Bet Placed (Waiting for Result)**\n3. **`close-call-page-connected-bet-placed`** — Wallet connected, userBet set, round still open\n   - Side selector shows selected state (user's chosen side highlighted)\n   - Buttons disabled (can't change bet)\n   - \"Your potential payout\" shown in pool distribution\n\n#### **Round Result — User Won (Green)**\n4. **`close-call-page-result-green-wins`** — completedRound.outcome=\"green\", user bet green\n   - Green result banner: \"GREEN WINS — You Won! +0.5234 SOL\"\n   - \"Payout Received!\" message in sidebar\n\n#### **Round Result — User Lost (Red)**\n5. **`close-call-page-result-red-wins-user-lost`** — completedRound.outcome=\"red\", user bet green\n   - Red result banner: \"RED WINS — You Lost -0.5000 SOL\"\n\n#### **Round Result — Refund**\n6. **`close-call-page-result-refund`** — completedRound.outcome=\"refund\"\n   - Yellow/gold banner: \"REFUND — Bet refunded\"\n\n#### **Pool States**\n7. **`close-call-page-balanced-pool`** — 50/50 green/red split\n8. **`close-call-page-skewed-pool-green`** — Green pool much larger (e.g., 75% green, 25% red)\n9. **`close-call-page-skewed-pool-red`** — Red pool much larger (e.g., 20% green, 80% red)\n\n#### **Round Details Page**\n10. **`close-call-roundid-loading`** — Pending fetch\n11. **`close-call-roundid-settled`** — Completed round with all data filled\n12. **`close-call-roundid-error-404`** — Round not found\n\n---\n\n### **6. CURRENT TEST BASELINE STATUS**\n\nThe existing `routes.spec.ts` already tests:\n```typescript\ntest(\"close call page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/close-call\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"close-call.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\nThis is a **basic route baseline** but does NOT cover state variations. It only captures the default \"loading\" or \"initial\" state.\n\n---\n\n### **7. TESTING INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\nThe testing fixture is already set up in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`:\n\n- **stablePage** fixture provides:\n  - Deterministic PRNG seed (Math.random, crypto.getRandomValues)\n  - Frozen Date.now (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n  - Animation freeze (CSS + SVG)\n  - Automatic font loading + network idle wait\n  - Console error detection (with noise filtering)\n\n---\n\n### **8. KEY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES FOR TESTS**\n\n1. **Mock Wallet**: Use the pattern from `states.spec.ts`:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.addInitScript(() => {\n     localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\");\n   });\n   ```\n   Then click `.rng-wallet-button--disconnected` to connect.\n\n2. **Wait for Component Render**: After navigation or interaction:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.waitForSelector(\".close-call-main\", { timeout: 10_000 });\n   ```\n\n3. **Freeze Animations After Interaction**: After clicking buttons:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.addStyleTag({ content: FREEZE_CSS });\n   ```\n\n4. **Component Selectors Available**:\n   - `.close-call-main` — main game area\n   - `.close-call-sidebar` — bet controls\n   - `.close-call-side-selector` — GREEN/RED buttons\n   - `.close-call-bet-input` — amount input\n   - `.close-call-pool-bar` — pool distribution\n   - `.close-call-page` — root container\n\n5. **Backend API**: The page fetches from `/closecall/current-round` and `/closecall/history`. In mock mode, these will fail (404), which is expected. The fixture filters \"401/403/429\" console errors.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\nClose-call has **rich visual state variation**:\n- **Wallet connectivity** (connected/disconnected)\n- **Round phases** (open betting, settled, refunded)\n- **User bet status** (no bet, placing, placed)\n- **Pool distributions** (balanced, skewed green, skewed red)\n- **Results** (green win, red win, refund, user won/lost/refunded)\n- **Chart state** (loading, rendered, different candle formations)\n\nThe existing test infrastructure is **ready**. You can add comprehensive state tests to `states.spec.ts` following the exact pattern used for Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs pages."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aadf28f5f88352357 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 75469\ntool_uses: 26\nduration_ms: 105768</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c8c62976-263f-4cf9-9e61-e0f9f45b35cf","uuid":"e6218060-2884-4b1a-9ad0-2486eadf8e7c","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the close-call frontend to understand what routes and states need visual coverage:\n\n1. Read `apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx` (the main page)\n2. Read `apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` (the deep-link round page)\n3. Read `apps/platform/src/App.tsx` for the close-call routes\n4. Check if there are any close-call specific state variations that could be visually tested (connected wallet, different phases, etc.)\n\nI need to understand what visual states are possible for close-call pages.","agentId":"aadf28f5f88352357","content":[{"type":"text","text":"### **1. ROUTES**\n\nThe close-call game has **two routes**:\n\n| Route | Component | Purpose |\n|-------|-----------|---------|\n| `/close-call` | `CloseCallPage.tsx` | Main game lobby with bet UI, candlestick chart, history |\n| `/close-call/:roundId` | `CloseCallRoundPage.tsx` | Deep-link to individual completed round details (fairness verification) |\n\n---\n\n### **2. VISUAL STATES FOR `/close-call` (Main Page)**\n\nThe `CloseCallPage` supports multiple visual variations based on context:\n\n#### **A. Wallet State**\n- **Disconnected** — \"Connect Wallet\" button visible in sidebar\n- **Connected** — \"GREEN\" / \"RED\" side selector buttons enabled\n\n#### **B. Betting Window State**\n- **Betting Open** (round.phase === \"open\" && now < bettingEndsAt)\n  - Side selector buttons enabled\n  - Bet amount input enabled\n  - User can place bets\n- **Betting Closed** (now >= bettingEndsAt)\n  - Side selector buttons disabled\n  - Message: \"Betting window closed\"\n- **Round Settled** (round.phase === \"settled\" or \"refunded\")\n  - Result banner displays outcome (GREEN WINS / RED WINS / REFUND)\n  - Pool distribution shows final state\n  - Winners get \"Payout Received!\" message\n\n#### **C. User Bet Status**\n- **No Bet Placed** — pending amount > 0, no userBet\n- **Bet Pending** (placingBet === true) — \"Joining...\" spinner on selected side button\n- **Bet Placed** (userBet !== null) — side button shows selected state, can't place another bet\n- **Round Result** (completedRound !== null) — result banner shows if user won/lost\n\n#### **D. Loading State**\n- **Loading Chart** (loading === true) — spinner + \"Loading chart...\" message\n- **Chart Ready** (recentCandles.length > 0) — candlestick chart renders\n\n#### **E. Chart & Pool States**\n- **Balanced Pool** (greenPool ≈ redPool) — bar split ~50/50\n- **Skewed Pool** (greenPool >> redPool or vice versa) — bar heavily weighted to one side\n- **Chart Progress** (candleProgress 0-1) — current candle progresses toward close\n- **Candlestick Colors** — green candles (close > open), red candles (close < open)\n\n#### **F. Pool Distribution UI**\n- **Pool Bar** — visual split showing GREEN% vs RED%\n- **Odds Display** — multiplier for each side (2.5x, 1.2x, etc.)\n- **Pool Amounts** — total SOL in each side\n\n#### **G. Result Banner (Post-Round)**\n- **Green Wins** (outcome === \"green\") — green banner, \"GREEN WINS\"\n- **Red Wins** (outcome === \"red\") — red banner, \"RED WINS\"\n- **Refund** (outcome === \"refund\") — yellow/gold banner, \"REFUND\"\n- **User Won** — \"You Won!\" + green payout amount\n- **User Lost** — \"You Lost\" + red loss amount\n- **Bet Refunded** — \"Bet refunded\" + no payout shown\n\n#### **H. History Modal**\n- Opened by clicking history entry\n- Shows: Round stats, candle OHLC data, outcome, your payout, oracle verification\n\n---\n\n### **3. VISUAL STATES FOR `/close-call/:roundId` (Round Details Page)**\n\nThis is a **static information page** showing completed round data with minimal state variance:\n\n#### **States:**\n- **Loading** — \"Loading round...\" spinner\n- **Error** (404) — \"Round not found\" message + back link\n- **Success** — Full round details:\n  - Round ID, status, creation time\n  - Oracle prices (open, close, change)\n  - Pool breakdown (green/red amounts and counts)\n  - Entries list (individual bets from both sides)\n  - Settlement info (if settled)\n  - Verification message explaining fairness model\n\n---\n\n### **4. COMPONENT VARIANTS**\n\nKey components with visual variations:\n\n| Component | File | Variations |\n|-----------|------|-----------|\n| **SideSelector** | `SideSelector.tsx` | disabled, selected, placing (spinner), disabled+other-placing |\n| **BetAmountInput** | `BetAmountInput.tsx` | disabled, with different max amounts |\n| **PoolDistribution** | `PoolDistribution.tsx` | pre-round (no outcome), post-round (with outcome highlight), various pool balances |\n| **CandlestickChart** | `CandlestickChart.tsx` | loading, rendering, candle progress, history vs current candle |\n| **RoundResultBanner** | Uses @rng-utopia/ui | green win, red win, refund, user won, user lost |\n\n---\n\n### **5. RECOMMENDED VISUAL TEST COVERAGE**\n\nBased on the pattern from `states.spec.ts`, here are the tests that should be created:\n\n#### **Disconnected User Tests**\n1. **`close-call-page-disconnected`** — Main page, betting open, wallet disconnected\n   - Shows \"Connect Wallet\" button instead of side selector\n\n#### **Connected User — Betting Open (Active Round)**\n2. **`close-call-page-connected-betting-open`** — Wallet connected, round.phase=\"open\", betting window active\n   - Side selector buttons enabled\n   - Bet amount input ready\n   - Pool bar showing current distribution\n   - Chart displaying candles\n\n#### **Connected User — Bet Placed (Waiting for Result)**\n3. **`close-call-page-connected-bet-placed`** — Wallet connected, userBet set, round still open\n   - Side selector shows selected state (user's chosen side highlighted)\n   - Buttons disabled (can't change bet)\n   - \"Your potential payout\" shown in pool distribution\n\n#### **Round Result — User Won (Green)**\n4. **`close-call-page-result-green-wins`** — completedRound.outcome=\"green\", user bet green\n   - Green result banner: \"GREEN WINS — You Won! +0.5234 SOL\"\n   - \"Payout Received!\" message in sidebar\n\n#### **Round Result — User Lost (Red)**\n5. **`close-call-page-result-red-wins-user-lost`** — completedRound.outcome=\"red\", user bet green\n   - Red result banner: \"RED WINS — You Lost -0.5000 SOL\"\n\n#### **Round Result — Refund**\n6. **`close-call-page-result-refund`** — completedRound.outcome=\"refund\"\n   - Yellow/gold banner: \"REFUND — Bet refunded\"\n\n#### **Pool States**\n7. **`close-call-page-balanced-pool`** — 50/50 green/red split\n8. **`close-call-page-skewed-pool-green`** — Green pool much larger (e.g., 75% green, 25% red)\n9. **`close-call-page-skewed-pool-red`** — Red pool much larger (e.g., 20% green, 80% red)\n\n#### **Round Details Page**\n10. **`close-call-roundid-loading`** — Pending fetch\n11. **`close-call-roundid-settled`** — Completed round with all data filled\n12. **`close-call-roundid-error-404`** — Round not found\n\n---\n\n### **6. CURRENT TEST BASELINE STATUS**\n\nThe existing `routes.spec.ts` already tests:\n```typescript\ntest(\"close call page\", async ({ stablePage }) => {\n  await stablePage.goto(\"/close-call\");\n  await expect(stablePage).toHaveScreenshot(\"close-call.png\", { fullPage: true });\n});\n```\n\nThis is a **basic route baseline** but does NOT cover state variations. It only captures the default \"loading\" or \"initial\" state.\n\n---\n\n### **7. TESTING INFRASTRUCTURE**\n\nThe testing fixture is already set up in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/fixtures.ts`:\n\n- **stablePage** fixture provides:\n  - Deterministic PRNG seed (Math.random, crypto.getRandomValues)\n  - Frozen Date.now (2026-01-01T00:00:00Z)\n  - Animation freeze (CSS + SVG)\n  - Automatic font loading + network idle wait\n  - Console error detection (with noise filtering)\n\n---\n\n### **8. KEY IMPLEMENTATION NOTES FOR TESTS**\n\n1. **Mock Wallet**: Use the pattern from `states.spec.ts`:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.addInitScript(() => {\n     localStorage.removeItem(\"rng-utopia-mock-wallet\");\n   });\n   ```\n   Then click `.rng-wallet-button--disconnected` to connect.\n\n2. **Wait for Component Render**: After navigation or interaction:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.waitForSelector(\".close-call-main\", { timeout: 10_000 });\n   ```\n\n3. **Freeze Animations After Interaction**: After clicking buttons:\n   ```typescript\n   await stablePage.addStyleTag({ content: FREEZE_CSS });\n   ```\n\n4. **Component Selectors Available**:\n   - `.close-call-main` — main game area\n   - `.close-call-sidebar` — bet controls\n   - `.close-call-side-selector` — GREEN/RED buttons\n   - `.close-call-bet-input` — amount input\n   - `.close-call-pool-bar` — pool distribution\n   - `.close-call-page` — root container\n\n5. **Backend API**: The page fetches from `/closecall/current-round` and `/closecall/history`. In mock mode, these will fail (404), which is expected. The fixture filters \"401/403/429\" console errors.\n\n---\n\n### **Summary**\n\nClose-call has **rich visual state variation**:\n- **Wallet connectivity** (connected/disconnected)\n- **Round phases** (open betting, settled, refunded)\n- **User bet status** (no bet, placing, placed)\n- **Pool distributions** (balanced, skewed green, skewed red)\n- **Results** (green win, red win, refund, user won/lost/refunded)\n- **Chart state** (loading, rendered, different candle formations)\n\nThe existing test infrastructure is **ready**. You can add comprehensive state tests to `states.spec.ts` following the exact pattern used for Coinflip and Lord of the RNGs pages."}],"totalDurationMs":105768,"totalTokens":75469,"totalToolUseCount":26,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":278,"cache_read_input_tokens":72598,"output_tokens":2588,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":278},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
